Ethiopian Airlines has received commendation from Airbus, aircraft manufacturer for the unique agility and resilience that it displayed amid the COVID-19 pandemic, which grounded activities for most parts of the year. A statement by the media consultant to the airline in Nigeria said that the airline was excited with the award and promised to consistently maintain standards in the sector. Mr. Tewolde GebreMariam, Ethiopian Group Chief Executive Officer (GCEO)in his comment said the airline was immensely delighted that one of the top companies in the world, Airbus, had recognised the efforts of the management and employees of the airline during the global crisis. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! “We were there when the world needed us most. I would like to express my gratitude to the over 17 thousand hardworking Ethiopian employees and management team,” he added. Mr. Hadi Akoum, Airbus Vice President Sales Africa commented that the award was to express the admiration of Airbus executive management and Airbus whole employees for the unbelievable achievement of Ethiopian Airlines in this unprecedented epidemic. Emirates Introduces Biofuel Powered, Environmentally Friendly A380s BREAKING: Chaos At Nnamdi Azikiwe Airport As Passengers Destroy Airlines’ Counters, Gadgets Over Delayed Flights Akoum noted that while other airlines were trying to figure out what to do, Ethiopia Airlines was aggressively pressing ahead finding solution, creating solution converting their passenger aircraft to freighters. He emphasised that the airline was the first one to do it on A350 and continued to fly and create even new business, describing it as a unique experience worldwide. He added: “Today, Ethiopian Airlines is able to maintain the operation of all fleet where others are at 10 per cent of their capability, and many airlines have just simply gone bankrupt and people have lost their jobs. This has been done because of the visionary leadership, Mr. Tewolde GebreMariam. “Ethiopian Airlines today is showing the example to the whole world in resilience and visionary thinking of the leadership. Thank you very much; it is a real admiration that we express at Airbus for your leadership and for Ethiopian Airlines Employees.” Ethiopian Airlines was the first airline that converted A350 passenger aircraft to cargo to transport the much needed medical supplies to combat the spread of Covid-19. The Airline is now operating 16 A350 aircraft in its networ SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION